                                         "email":  "drhalilmurattasci@users.noreply.github.com",
                                         "date":  "2026-05-30T16:52:04Z"
                                     },
                       "message":  "PROJECT-SAVE-WIRING: route Ctrl+S by SaveSource (Scene/Project), replacing scene_source_path\n\nPart 2 of in-app .rge-project save. Replaces the editor-shell\n`scene_source_path: Option\u003cPathBuf\u003e` with a unified `save_source:\nOption\u003cSaveSource\u003e` (Scene | Project) so a scene-source and a project-source\ncannot both be set (illegal state unrepresentable), and routes Ctrl+S by variant:\n- Scene   -\u003e SceneSaveHook (save_scene_world_to_path), silent overwrite\n- Project -\u003e new ProjectSaveHook (save_project_world_to_path), silent write\n- None    -\u003e Save-As (commits a Scene source)\n\nOpen + --scene commit Scene for `.rge-scene` and Project for a literal\n`.rge-project`. The binary owns the loader edge via a new ProjectSaveWriterHook\n(mirrors SceneSaveWriterHook); editor-shell stays free of rge-scene-loader /\nrge-data (no Cargo.toml change). Title + status bar derive their file name from\nsave_source_path() (v0: the literal .rge-project for a project).\n\n10 files: 8 editor-shell/binary + 2 surfaced scene_source_path consumers\n(tests/save_status_snapshot_smoke.rs, editor-state doc) ported per the TASK\nhalt condition. No scene_source_path symbol remains.\n\nGate: VERIFY OK (7/7), 10/10 arch lints; new project routing + disk round-trip\ntests green.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
