                       "message":  "PROJECT-SAVE-WIRING: stale-prose sweep — widen scene-only save-status/title docs to save-source wording (post-exec doc fix)\n\nPost-exec correction (doc/comment-only; no logic change). After widening the\nsave source model to scene-or-project, several save-status / window-title docs\nstill described the snapshot / handoff / status bar as an open-scene name.\nSwept the repo and updated them to save-source / document wording:\n\n- editor-state SaveStatusSnapshot module + field docs\n- editor-egui-host status-bar chrome (lib.rs x4) + handoff alias doc\n- editor-shell render_path publish comments (x2) + lifecycle field/title comments\n- editor-shell save-status smoke test header + message; window-title test header\n- editor-ui save_status widget doc + test comment (removed the now-false\n  rge-project-under-No-scene framing; an open project surfaces its name)\n\nThe rendered No-scene empty-state string and the scene_file_name field name are\nleft as-is (no logic change requested) and noted as cosmetic follow-ups.\n\nGate: VERIFY OK (7/7), 10/10 arch lints. scene_source_path stays retired.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
